{# Docs landing page #}

<section class="docs-content">
  <p>
    FeedMyOwl is a minimalist RSS and Atom reader built around one question:
    does this help you read better, or does it distract you?
  </p>

  <h2>Core Principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No unread counts, badges, or urgency mechanics.</li>
    <li>No push notifications; refresh is always user-driven.</li>
    <li>No social layer, reactions, or recommendation loops.</li>
    <li>Typography and whitespace are treated as product features.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How To Use FeedMyOwl</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Add your feed subscriptions.</li>
    <li>Press refresh when you want new entries.</li>
    <li>Use search or keyboard shortcuts to move through articles quickly.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="article-search">Article search</h2>
  <p>
    Search is always available at the top of the article list pane in the feeds workspace.
    It is global across loaded articles, even if a folder or feed scope is selected.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Type at least 2 characters to activate fuzzy matching.</li>
    <li>Results are ranked by relevance, then recency.</li>
    <li>The list shows up to the top 50 matches.</li>
    <li>Matched text is highlighted in article and feed titles.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="keyboard-shortcuts">Keyboard shortcuts</h2>
  <p>
    Keyboard shortcuts are available in the feeds workspace on desktop and tablet.
    Shortcuts are disabled on mobile layout and while typing in a text field.
  </p>

  <h3>Navigation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>j</code>: Select next article (list or reader).</li>
    <li><code>k</code>: Select previous article (list or reader).</li>
    <li><code>ArrowDown</code>: Select next article (list only).</li>
    <li><code>ArrowUp</code>: Select previous article (list only).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Reading actions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>Enter</code>: Open selected article (list only).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>App actions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>r</code>: Refresh feeds.</li>
    <li><code>/</code>: Focus article search.</li>
    <li><code>?</code>: Open keyboard shortcuts help.</li>
    <li><code>Escape</code>: Close the shortcuts dialog, or clear search when focused.</li>
  </ul>

